## What happened

Creating a new Project on IntelliJ IDEA, it show me only 3 files f_demo7.iml, f_demo7.ipr, f_demo.iws.
But if I run Flutter create f_demo7 on the command line, it creates the project normally.

I am using Windows 10, and a new Flutter installation using master branch, and also run flutter doctor.

comment_data.body: I also run IntelliJ IDEA as admin, still the same error.
Your IDEA and Flutter plugins are a little our of date. Can you try with IDEA 2017.1 and Flutter plugin 13.1?

I installed again, still got issues on it

I will see if I can get the error message from this new version

This might be related with this issue: https://www.java-forums.org/advanced-java/63494-java-io-ioexception-cannot-run-program-cmd-exe-createprocess-error-5-access-denied.html

I am unistalling java from my computer and reinstalling it again

Ok, I solve the issue... it is not flutter or intellijIdea the issue. It has to do with the git version I have installed in my computer, that messes the permissions on flutter folder... I will attach some screenshots...

![flutter_git_folder_creation](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7681091/25950299/5cbc7bfe-3652-11e7-927a-1d4bc713162d.PNG)

![flutter_git_folder_creation_1](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7681091/25950356/9dca2812-3652-11e7-9b3d-289d9581ada3.PNG)


The folder gets created, but doesn't allow me to execute the flutter.bat.

This ticket can be close... thanks for the help
Ah, great to hear! Just for future support cases: which version of git for windows caused this?

It is a weird one:
I just reinstall https://git-scm.com/download/win

git version 2.8.3

I did two tests: I run git clone using Windows CMD.exe and also Git Bash.

![flutter_git_folder_creation_2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7681091/25951555/fa4423e2-3655-11e7-8ddb-b3c40996a0d9.PNG)

Git clone using CMD.exe doesnt work, while git bash works fine, no issues with permissions

Using the folder created using git clone on "git bash". All works fine

![flutter_git_folder_creation_3](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7681091/25951730/7442f2fe-3656-11e7-9666-9ab5ed972f9e.PNG)

Wow.  Thanks @claudfernandes for all the thoughtful follow-up!

cc @alexander-doroshko as an FYI.
